    <h3>Check Your Box Spring (If You Have One)</h3>

    <p>Box springs last longer than mattresses generally, but they don't last forever. After 10-15+ years, the internal components can break down.</p>

    <p>Run your hand along the entire surface of the box spring. Feel for any metal or wood that is bent, cracked, or broken. If any spot feels soft, sunken, or uneven, the box spring is compromised.</p>

    <p><strong>A broken box spring will cause uneven support, which leads to sagging and body impressions in your new mattress</strong> — even if the mattress itself is perfect.</p>

