    <h3>For RV Owners</h3>

    <p><strong>Check your clearance:</strong> Before ordering, measure the depth/height that fits in your RV. Some RV beds are under a folding table, counter, or cabinet that limits how thick your mattress can be. A 14" luxury mattress won't work if you only have 10" of clearance.</p>

    <p><strong>Check for odd cutouts:</strong> Some Full XL RV beds have a notch, rounded corner, or angled edge to fit the RV layout. If the cutout is minor, you can often purchase an all-foam mattress and let it compress around the shape. For more complex cutouts, you may need a custom shop.</p>
