<!-- FAQ -->
<section id="faq" class="faq-section">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What size is a Full XL mattress?</h3>
        <p>A Full XL mattress measures 54 inches wide by 80 inches long. It's 5 inches longer than a standard Full (54×75) while maintaining the same width.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is Full XL the same as Queen?</h3>
        <p>No. This is a common point of confusion. A Full XL (54×80) and Queen (60×80) have the same 80-inch length, but a Queen is 6 inches wider. They are not interchangeable sizes.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Will Full sheets fit a Full XL mattress?</h3>
        <p>No. Full sheets are designed for a 54×75 mattress and will be 5 inches too short on a Full XL. The fitted sheet will constantly pop off the corners. Use Full XL sheets (54×80) or Queen sheets with straps to secure the extra width.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Will Queen sheets fit a Full XL mattress?</h3>
        <p>Queen sheets can work as a temporary solution. They have the correct 80-inch length but are 6 inches wider than needed. The fitted sheet will be loose and baggy. Use sheet straps/suspenders to keep them in place.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Will a Full XL mattress fit on a standard Full frame?</h3>
        <p>No. A standard Full frame is designed for a 54×75 mattress. A Full XL mattress (54×80) will hang 5 inches over the end, unsupported. This causes problems for both the mattress and the frame. You need a Full XL specific frame.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Where can I buy a Full XL bed frame?</h3>
        <p>Full XL frames are available from Wayfair, Amazon (search "Full XL bed frame" or "54×80 bed frame"), Rest Right Mattress, and some local furniture stores. Platform beds work well — just ensure the dimensions are 54×80.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How long does a Full XL mattress last?</h3>
        <p>With quality materials, 7-10 years is typical. However, we regularly see Full XL mattresses that are 10-15 years old — not because they last longer, but because owners don't know where to buy replacements. Don't sleep on a worn-out mattress. Replace it when support degrades.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What's the best Full XL mattress for a tall person?</h3>
        <p>Any of our recommendations work for tall sleepers — the 80-inch length accommodates heights up to 6'6" comfortably. The Sedona Elite is best if you want luxury quality. The Dreamfoam Essential (10" or thicker) is best on a budget.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What's the best Full XL mattress for an RV?</h3>
        <p>It depends on your priorities: Dreamfoam Essential (6-8" if low clearance, 10" if you have room) for budget; Mattress Insider Natural Latex for temperature consistency; Mattress Insider Luxury Gel Foam for flippable firmness.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What's the best Full XL mattress for a guest room?</h3>
        <p>Dreamfoam Essential (8-10") — comfortable enough for guests, affordable enough for occasional use.</p>
    </div>
